        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 5:23PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 523 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Raton, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Raton and Sugarite.

This includes the following highways...
Highway 64 between Mile Markers 343 and 364.
Interstate 25 between Mile Markers 445 and 459.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Motorists can expect brief but sudden changes in visibility and
ponding of water on roadways as storms move through the area.</instruction>
